Reasoning: The paper deals with the detection of online discussion topics manipulated by OSM abusers, which falls under the category of social media analysis. The proposed approach involves the analysis and classification of OSM accounts, which can be categorized under machine learning and data mining. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other possible sub-categories include cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.SD (Software Engineering), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
